Henry Street, west side, north from a point midway between Love Lane and Clark Street, viewing toward the latter. In the foreground is the First Presbyterian Church, erected in 1846, and about two hundred feet away is the First Methodist Episcopal Church, at the S.W. corner of Clark Street. At the N.W. corner is the Hotel St. George (views 2,3).

View 1: Eugene L. Armbruster Collection

Views 2,3: P. L. Sperr

View 2: March 1, 1929
View 3: April 4, 1932
